This paper deals with secure skyline computation on encrypted datasets, which is a topic that falls under the database (cs.DB) and cryptography (cs.CR) sub-categories. The paper also proposes algorithms for pre-computation of skyline results, which involves dynamic programming and greedy heuristics, and this falls under the data structures (cs.DS) and computational complexity (cs.CC) sub-categories. Finally, the paper focuses on the encrypted setting, which is related to distributed computing (cs.DC).
